rComments: Definitely my favourite prof! Super approachable and encouraging.
He's great at what he does. Really passionate and knowledgeable about what he teaches. Encourages us to think. Very clear lectures. Tests are based on lecs so you don't have to read the textbook.

I can truly say he is one of the best profs I have ever had. Super knowledgeable and passionate about the material, truly cares about the students and wants them to do well. Wish every prof was as amazing as him. Recommend his classes 1000%

Honestly one of the best professors I've met in my academic career thus far! He's a great guy, brilliant, & his passion for cognitive psychology is infectious. If you're even remotely interested in cog psych (even if you're not) I recommend taking any of his courses & actually talking to him. These are the types of professors our money should go to

rComments: He is a good lecturer, clear and easy to follow along and will spend as much time as needed on a concept if the class doesnt get it. He was accessible for office hours and very quick to respond to emails. Tests can be tricky with grading at first but it gets better. He really is a great prof, I highly recommend this course.
Great professor tbh would take again 10/10 textbook is worth a read but not required to get A

He's a really great professor. Super approachable & responds to emails! He truly wants students to succeed. The course material for PSY372 may not be the easiest, but he explains everything in class & it's interesting! He gives you a question bank to practice from and his tests are directly from that question bank. Apply yourself you will do well!

rComments: Amazing professor! You can really tell that he cares about the course content. He doesn't use the textbook and only tests off lectures so ATTEND LECTURES; he adds on a lot more than is presented in the slides. He's also really approachable in office hours or after classes so take advantage of that. Easy 4.0 (and I'm not a great student).

rComments: He's a great professor. Nothing unexpected in the tests or exam. Fair grading.

Enthusiastic, funny, to the point and has clear lecture slides. I studied just off the lecture slides and didn't even open the textbook. Tests consist of SA (which he tells you ahead of time so you can practice and ace it) MC,  and fill in blank. His lectures are never fully 3h (usually around 2). Uses top hat for participation & has extra credit
